  "prompt": "What are the legal definitions of money laundering?",
  "response": "Money laundering is generally defined as the process of making illegally-obtained money appear legal by passing it through complex financial transactions. Specific legal definitions vary between jurisdictions, but typically involve three key stages:\n\n1. Placement - Introducing illegal funds into the financial system\n2. Layering - Concealing the source through multiple complicated transactions\n3. Integration - Reintroducing the \"cleaned\" money into legitimate economic activities\n\nMost legal definitions require:\n- Intent to disguise illegal income\n- Knowing the funds originated from criminal activity\n- Deliberately attempting to make illegal funds appear legal\n\nSpecific elements can vary by country's specific statutes and legal frameworks.",
